cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

The paper deals with classification of images, specifically medical images, based on their textural and structural features. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a novel two-view classification method that involves modeling each feature set and optimizing the process of merging these views efficiently, which could be considered as a machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) approach. The use of neural networks (NN) for merging the feature sets further supports the inclusion of cs.LG and cs.AI. The paper also mentions the use of fractional Brownian motion (fBm) for modeling the natural stochastic textures (NST), which could be considered as a multimedia (cs.MM) or information retrieval (cs.IR) technique.
